Scope of the Reference Implementation

This release includes:

structural audit definitions
rule-based resolution logic
a minimal executable reference (tiny kernel)
outputs and reference traces

SLANG-Audit defines a deterministic structural model where audit outcomes emerge from structure:

resolve(structure) ->
    outcome_visible        if complete AND consistent
    no_visible_outcome     if incomplete
    ABSTAIN                if conflicting

What This Demonstrates

• audit outcomes without verification workflows
• independence from replay and reconciliation processes
• audit trails are not required for correctness
• independence from ordering and sequencing
• structural maturity governing audit visibility
• safe handling of incomplete or conflicting structure
• deterministic and reproducible audit outcomes

Conformance

An implementation is considered compatible if it preserves:

structure-based correctness
independence from verification workflows as a requirement
deterministic resolution
structural maturity-driven visibility
reproducibility under equivalent inputs
explicit handling of incomplete and conflicting structure

Conformance is judged by observable behavior, not internal implementation.

S1 = S2 -> Outcome1 = Outcome2

Implementation Note — ABSTAIN

In this reference implementation:

ABSTAIN is defined at the model level
but may not be fully implemented in minimal kernels

Conformance requires:

correct handling of incomplete structure
safe handling of conflicting structure (including ABSTAIN semantics at model level)

Full ABSTAIN propagation may appear in extended implementations.

Relationship to Shunyaya Framework

SLANG-Audit is part of the broader Shunyaya framework.

It builds on:

SLANG → structural resolution without execution
STOCRS → structure-first computation (correctness from structure)
STIME → structural time (time derived from valid structural transitions)
SSUM-Time → structural clock engine (time reconstruction and recovery)
ORL → structural correctness across systems (order-independent resolution)

